<br>
Your arguement is very sound and compassionate. However the reason to wake the sleeper isn't about compassion fo other players. Its about denying competing guilds of resources that could help them. Its about maintaining / furthering a competitive advantage.<br>
<br>
If you think that sucks, well you'd be right. You'd also probably be not among the ranks of the guild that does wake the sleeper.<br>
<br>
Its a tactically wise move in a competitive environment, think about it like someone taking your &quot;queen&quot; in a game of chess. It gives your opponent an advantage over you, but it doesnt mean your opponent &quot;wins&quot; the game and it doesnt mean YOU can't still win. It just makes it harder.<br>
<br>
Do you disagree because you don't think the high end game in EQ is competitive? Or is it because this action would permanently remove an encounter and its associated rewards from the game? If its the former then we could start a whole new thread about EQ and the high end game. If its the latter then you can't be mad at Reso or anyone who wakes the sleeper. You should be mad at Verant for designing the encounter that way. <p>Kzan Verto<BR>
